    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-20T18:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-20T18:00:00-05:00" n="763"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d763">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 652.119/1976</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in France</hi> (<persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Sharp</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-20T23:00:00+00:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 20, 1918, 11 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                        <lb/> [<hi rend="italic">Received October 21, 2.55 p.m.</hi>]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>5498. Personal for <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MVC1"
                        >McCormick</persName>, War Trade Board [from <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName>]:</p>
                <p>No. 519. Department No. 5924, October 16, War Trade Board 385.<note n="1"
                        xml:id="d763fn1">See footnote 1, <hi rend="italic">ante</hi>, <ref
                            target="#pg_1711">p. 1711</ref>.</note> Lack of animal supplies is
                    become a most serious problem of A.E.F. For example, some divisions are
                    practically immobile in consequence thereof. The remount officers state that the
                    supplies of mules in Spain are quite sufficient for national requirements of
                    Spain but even if same are insufficient, mules will not be required again in
                    quantity until the spring and many things may happen. In the meantime something
                    must be done. It is quite possible Spanish Government for one reason or another
                    will again refuse to release mules, notwithstanding your offer of ammonia, and
                    under such circumstances we venture to suggest most vigorous diplomatic
                    representations and, if necessary, drastic blockade policy, if you think by such
                    procedure the release of mules can be secured. We send this cable on the urgent
                    solicitation of the military advisers of the A.E.F. <persName
                        corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_MG1">McFadden</persName>.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SWG1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Sharp</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
